The paper deals with decentralized caching in two-layer networks, which involves designing algorithms for data delivery and exploiting correlations between layers to reduce transmission rates. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with caching, which is a topic that falls under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the design of algorithms, which could place it under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of achievable rate regions, which could place it under the Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-category.
